speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for the Home Department (1) whether he will give an undertaking that all cases of naturalised aliens who have been, or shall be, con-


victed of offences against war-time regulations shall be referred to the appropriate committee, with a view to the revocation of their certificates of naturalisation;

(2) whether he will state the names and qualifications of the members of the committee appointed under Section 7 of the British Nationality and Status of Aliens Act; and how many cases, and with what results, have been referred to this committee since the outbreak of the war?
